[[File:Sogatsuhiko-jinja, torii.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Torii gate}}]]
'''Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine''' (そがにますそがつひこじんじゃ<ref>[http://www.narashinsei.com/search/%E3%82%B5%E8%A1%8C/%E5%AE%97%E6%88%91%E5%9D%90%E5%AE%97%E6%88%91%E9%83%BD%E6%AF%94%E5%8F%A4%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE/ Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine] (Nara Prefecture Association of Shinto Shrines).</ref>/そがにいますそがつひこじんじや{{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Heibonsha)|1981}}/そがのそがつひこじんじゃ{{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Kami-gami)|2000}}) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in Soga-chō, {{jalink|Kashihara City|Q496319}}, {{jalink|Nara Prefecture|Q131287}}. It is a {{jalink|Shikinaisha}} (major shrine), and under the {{jalink|modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|former shrine rank}} it was classified as a {{jalink|village shrine|Q134917284}}.

It is also commonly known as “Iruka-no-miya.” The shrine is known as being associated with the ancient powerful clan, the {{jalink|Soga clan|Q909854}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
The enshrined deities are the following two {{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Kami-gami)|2000}}:
:* '''Sogatsuhiko-no-Kami''' (そがつひこのかみ, also written 宗我都比古神)
:* '''Sogatsuhime-no-Kami''' (そがつひめのかみ, also written 宗我都比売神)

In the {{jalink|Engishiki|Q1342448}} {{jalink|Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|Register of Deities}} compiled in {{jalink|Enchō|Q1327274|Enchō}} 5 ({{jalink|927|Q30470}}), the shrine is listed as having two seats of deities. The entry records the name as “Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine,” meaning “the shrine that enshrines Sogatsuhiko in Soga (= Soga/Soga/Soga: a place name).” One of the two seats is identified as Sogatsuhiko-no-Kami, but the identity of the other seat is unclear.

=== About the enshrined deities ===
<div class="thumb tright">
 <div style="margin: 0px; padding: 2px; border: 1px solid #a2a9b1; text-align: center; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; text-align:center; font-size:80%">
'''Genealogy of the {{jalink|Soga clan|Q909854}}'''
