[[File:Sogatsuhiko-jinja, torii.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Torii gate}}]]
'''Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine''' (そがにますそがつひこじんじゃ<ref>[http://www.narashinsei.com/search/%E3%82%B5%E8%A1%8C/%E5%AE%97%E6%88%91%E5%9D%90%E5%AE%97%E6%88%91%E9%83%BD%E6%AF%94%E5%8F%A4%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE/ Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine] (Nara Prefecture Association of Shinto Shrines).</ref>/そがにいますそがつひこじんじや{{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Heibonsha)|1981}}/そがのそがつひこじんじゃ{{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Kami-gami)|2000}}) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in Soga-chō, {{ill|lt=Kashihara City|Q496319|WD=Q496319|1=Kashihara, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} (major shrine), and under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} it was classified as a {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

It is also commonly known as “Iruka-no-miya.” The shrine is known as being associated with the ancient powerful clan, the {{ill|lt=Soga clan|Q909854|WD=Q909854|1=Soga clan}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
The enshrined deities are the following two {{Sfn|Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine (Kami-gami)|2000}}:
:* '''Sogatsuhiko-no-Kami''' (そがつひこのかみ, also written 宗我都比古神)
:* '''Sogatsuhime-no-Kami''' (そがつひめのかみ, also written 宗我都比売神)

In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki|Q1342448|WD=Q1342448|1=Engishiki}} {{ill|lt=Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Register of Deities|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} compiled in {{ill|lt=Enchō|Q1327274|WD=Q1327274|lt=Enchō|1=Enchō}} 5 ({{ill|lt=927|Q30470|WD=Q30470|1=927}}), the shrine is listed as having two seats of deities. The entry records the name as “Soga-ni-masu Sogatsuhiko Shrine,” meaning “the shrine that enshrines Sogatsuhiko in Soga (= Soga/Soga/Soga: a place name).” One of the two seats is identified as Sogatsuhiko-no-Kami, but the identity of the other seat is unclear.

=== About the enshrined deities ===
